<p><span class="spip_note_ref">[<a href='#nh2' class='spip_note' title='Notes 2' rev='footnote'>2</a>]&nbsp;</span>&#8220;Criminal networks are not only expanding their operations, but they are also diversifying their activities (...). These networks also threaten U.S. interests by forging alliances with corrupt elements of national governments and using the power and influence of those elements to further their criminal activities. In some cases, national governments exploit these relationships to further their interests&#8221; (&#171;&nbsp;Strategy to Combat Transnational Organized Crime&nbsp;&#187;, National Security Council, Washington, 25 juin 2011).</p>
